OL,3,CDonaldson abuse not reported as it
OL,4,Cwould 'destroy reputation', trial told
OL,6,FThe court was then played a police
OL,7,Fvideo interview from Pastor Stephen
OL,8,FMatthews, who had met Complainant B at
OL,9,Fthe Christian Family Centre.
OL,11,FHe is not well enough to give evidence
OL,12,Fto the trial.
OL,14,FIn his police interview, he said
OL,15,FComplainant B had been "emotionally
OL,16,Fdistressed" when she spoke to him.
OL,18,FHe said: "I spent time with her, I
OL,19,Fprayed with her."
OL,26,@wD@XOUxD@KO]zD@JOU{D@QO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G6/16
