OL,3,CDonaldson abuse not reported as it
OL,4,Cwould 'destroy reputation', trial told
OL,6,FThe court was then told about a
OL,7,Fmeeting between Donaldson, Complainant
OL,8,FB and the Hoys in their home in Armoy
OL,9,Fthe following day.
OL,11,FMr Hoy said: "Mr Donaldson spoke
OL,12,Ffirst, he said I know what this is
OL,13,Fabout, he said I am sorry and can you
OL,14,Fplease forgive me."
OL,16,FThe witness said that Complainant B
OL,17,Fwas upset but she "did say she forgave
OL,18,Fhim".
OL,26,@sD@NOUvD@SO]yD@SOUzD@DO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}           G12/16
